{
  "text": "Gdn-HCl-induced denaturation was done by titrating Gdn HCl from a 6 M stock solution to AFA-PLN at pH 6.0. Six additions were made to a final Gdn HCl concentration of 2.8 M, and [ 1 H, [CITATION_1] N] HSQC and [ 1 H, [CITATION_2] C] HSQC spectra were acquired after each addition as described above. For the analysis of unfolding, spectra were referenced to 10 mM 2,2-dimethyl-2-silapentane-5-sulfonate, and [CITATION_3] N peak shifts were plotted as a function of Gdn HCl concentration. The data were fit using the Hill equation:",
